postcontent: **If you contact me concerning this ad, ensure you check your spam folder for my response**This rifle was hand built by Ernst Steigleder sometime between 1898 and World War I ( Prewar ). The rifle  has double set triggers, which function flawless with an extremely light break when set.  This rifle also features Suhler Einhackmontage or claw mounts for the scope - meaning the scope can be removed to shoot with the iron sights or for traveling and then placed back on the rifle in 3 seconds with no change in zero.  These claw mounts have been modified with standard US 1" rings, which allow any American made scope to be used on the rifle.  A very nice feature which cannot be found in most claw mounts.  This rifle also comes with an El Paso made Weaver K4 with standard fine crosshair.  Optics are very good.  The rifle is extensively engraved, with the builders name stamped into the barrel.  A 'butterknife' or 'spoon' bolt handle enhances the elegance of this prewar German sporting rifle.  The bore is good with high lands, however there is some darkness in the groove.  The rifle is chambered in 8mm Mauser.  The front sight has been modified to accept both the enlongated sight insert as well as a typical barleycorn side to side sight insert.  No inserts are included with the rifle and should be customized to the buyers preference.  The original stock is missing, however the rifle comes in a very lovely military Mauser stock with almost perfect inletting and an extensive amount of tiger stripe figure.  Additional pictures of anything on the rifle - just ask.  Any questions you may have, just shoot me an email.  Check out the Husqvarna rifles I also have for sale.I will ship the rifle at the buyer's expense, but only to an authorized FFL.  If you are a PA resident, we can discuss further options.See my other ads for some other interesting old guns.Trade interests (I can add cash on my end or you can depending on the trade): BRNO sporter rifles, Oberndorf sporter rifles, BRNO 16 gauge sidelock, French shotguns ( Manufrance, Robust, Ideal, others) SKB 280e with English stock in 20, 28, or 410 V.
